From: Christian Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
Subject: [PATCH] meson: Use native zlib for genunifont

genunifont is a build-time code generator declared with native: true
in meson, but its zlib dependency was not declared as native. This
causes the native x86_64 executable to link against the target
aarch64 zlib, failing with "file in wrong format".

Add a separate native zlib dependency and use it for genunifont.

Upstream-Status: Pending

AI-Generated: Claude Opus 4.6
Signed-off-by: Christian Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
---
 meson.build     | 1 +
 src/meson.build | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -52,6 +52,7 @@
 dl_deps = dependency('dl')
 threads_deps = dependency('threads')
 zlib_deps = dependency('zlib')
+zlib_native_deps = dependency('zlib', native: true)

 python = find_program('python3')

--- a/src/meson.build
+++ b/src/meson.build
@@ -161,7 +161,7 @@
 # Unifont Generator
 # This generates the unifont sources from raw hex-encoded font data.
 #
-genunifont = executable('genunifont', 'genunifont.c', dependencies: [zlib_deps], native: true)
+genunifont = executable('genunifont', 'genunifont.c', dependencies: [zlib_native_deps], native: true)

 unifont_bin = custom_target('unifont-bin',
   input: ['font_unifont_data.hex'],
